 1. Objective of the Project
To understand how data structures are used in real-life applications
To implement a secure and fair voting system
To practice searching, storing, and updating data efficiently

 2. Concepts Used (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔹 1. Arrays
Used to store:
Candidates
Voter IDs
 Easy to manage multiple data items
🔹 2. Structures (struct)
Combines:
Candidate name
Vote count
 Makes data organized
🔹 3. String Handling
strcmp() → compare names
strcpy() → copy data
🔹 4. Searching Algorithm
Linear search is used:
To find candidate
To check duplicate voters
🔹 5. Counting Technique
Votes are counted by incrementing values

 3. Working of the System
 
 The program works in the following steps:
User enters number of candidates
Candidate names are stored
Menu is displayed:
Vote
Show Results
Exit
When voting:
Voter enters ID
System checks if already voted
If not → vote is recorded
Results show:
Total votes
Winner

 4. Features of the Project

✔ Simple and user-friendly interface
✔ Prevents duplicate voting
✔ Stores multiple candidates
✔ Displays real-time results
✔ Automatically finds winner

 5. Security Features
One voter → one vote
Duplicate checking using voter ID
Invalid candidate handling

 6. Advantages
Easy to understand and implement
Demonstrates real-world application of DSA
Efficient for small-scale voting
Helps learn data handling


